      • findUserSiteByUserIdCriteria

        protected Site findUserSiteByUserIdCriteria(String formSubmittedUserId)
        Searches for a user's workspace site by resolving the given ID to a User object and calculating the target Site's ID from that object. As implemented, supports user PK and EID inputs. Be aware that searching for users by EID can result in the lazy creation of Sakai user records, or at least user ID mapping records.
        Parameters:
        formSubmittedUserId - typically end-user provided search criteria; must not be null
        Returns:
        the user's workspace site or null if no such user or no such site
        See Also:
        findUserByPk(String), findUserByEid(String), findUserSite(User)

      • findUserByPk

        protected User findUserByPk(String userPk)
        Search for a User object by primary key (i.e. User.id).
        Parameters:
        userPk - a String to be treated as a user's Sakai-internal primary key; must not be null
        Returns:
        a resolved User or null, signifying no results
        See Also:
        UserDirectoryService.getUser(String)

      • findUserByEid

        protected User findUserByEid(String eid)
        Search for a User object by user "enterprise identifier", (i.e. User.eid).
        Parameters:
        eid - a String to be treated as a user's "enterprise identifier"; must not be null
        Returns:
        a resolved User or null, signifying no results
        See Also:
        UserDirectoryService.getUserByEid(String)

      • findUserSite

        protected Site findUserSite(User knownUser)
        Search for the given User's workspace Site.
        Parameters:
        knownUser - user having a Sakai primary key (doesn't necessarily mean the user has actually signed in yet). Must not be null
        Returns:
        the user's workspace site or null if no such thing, e.g. if the user has not yet logged in.
